FILE
	/usr/common/sys/exitd.c

NAME
	num_deferred_exits - return the current number of deferred exits

PROTOTYPE
	int num_deferred_exits(void)

CALLED BY
	System, Common, Game

DESCRIPTION
	See add_deferred_exits for an explanation of deferred exits.
	This function returns how many of them there are, MUD-wide.

RETURN VALUE
	The number of deferred exits, or -1 if that information can't
	be returned.

ERRORS
	Normally none.

SEE ALSO
	add_deferred_exits, add_twoway_exit_between
